Pre-Game Insights: Orlando Magic will be without their top four scorers and a reserve three-and-D guard, bringing a next-level challenge to the game.
The 8-25 Jazz are one of five NBA teams yet to surpass 10 wins, but they can't be counted out as non-competitive.
The Jazz have a below-average offense but excel in effective and true shooting percentage, offensive rating, and rebounding.
Utah is the NBA's most turnover-prone team and surrenders the most points off of their giveaways.
The Magic have the third-best home record in the NBA and need to capitalize on this opportunity.
The Magic's slate of games following Utah isn't easy, with games against New York, Minnesota, Milwaukee, and Philadelphia.
